[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello, I want to test Miguel's patch series with the rustc upgrade, I've applied the patchset on top of rust-next, and I assume I have to perform these additional steps, are they enough (assume config already has rust enabled)?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rustup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">override</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">min</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustc</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">rustup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">component</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">add</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>#<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">standard</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">library</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">source</span>\n<span class=\"n\">cargo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">install</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">locked</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">min</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tool</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">version</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindgen</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustavailable</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"cp\">$(</span><span class=\"n\">nproc</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(from <a href=\"https://wusyong.github.io/posts/rust-kernel-module-00/\">https://wusyong.github.io/posts/rust-kernel-module-00/</a>)</p>",
        "id": 351288455,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1681988941
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, that should work. If you have the wrong toolchain, then you should see a warning/error (depending if it is newer/older) -- you can test that you see the message by not upgrading the toolchain but applying the patches first, for instance.</p>\n<p>You can also double check the right compiler is getting used by e.g. <code>grep RUSTC_VERSION .config</code>.</p>\n<p>Thanks for testing the upgrade!</p>",
        "id": 351294513,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1681990274
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well, it didn't give me any error with 1.66.0, which I had set, it built successfully:<br>\noutput of <code>rustup override list</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">amiculas</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">work</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"w\">                       </span><span class=\"mf\">1.66.0</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">gnu</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now i've upgraded to 1.68.2 and it also built successfully.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">amiculas</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">work</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"w\">                       </span><span class=\"mf\">1.68.2</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">gnu</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>grep RUSTC_VERSION .config</code> doesn't show me anything though.</p>",
        "id": 351299240,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1681991330
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>rustavailable</code> gives me this error when the toolchain is older:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"err\">❯</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustavailable</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compiler</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">rustc</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">too</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">old</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Your</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span>:    <span class=\"mf\">1.66.0</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Minimum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span>: <span class=\"mf\">1.68.2</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">1825</span>: <span class=\"nc\">rustavailable</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but otherwise it seems to build with the older toolchain (I'm doing a rebuild now to confirm)</p>",
        "id": 351300409,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1681991628
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"607542\">Ariel Miculas</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Testing.20the.20rustc.20upgrade/near/351299240\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>well, it didn't give me any error with 1.66.0, which I had set, it built successfully:<br>\noutput of <code>rustup override list</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">amiculas</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">work</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"w\">                       </span><span class=\"mf\">1.66.0</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">gnu</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now i've upgraded to 1.68.2 and it also built successfully.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">amiculas</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">work</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"w\">                       </span><span class=\"mf\">1.68.2</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">unknown</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">gnu</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>grep RUSTC_VERSION .config</code> doesn't show me anything though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then it means Rust is not enabled, so there is no error (because then it does not matter which toolchain is installed). Please check that <code>make LLVM=1 rustavailable</code> is successful and printing \"Rust is available!\".</p>",
        "id": 351300414,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1681991630
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"607542\">Ariel Miculas</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Testing.20the.20rustc.20upgrade/near/351300409\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>rustavailable</code> gives me this error when the toolchain is older:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"err\">❯</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustavailable</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compiler</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">rustc</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">too</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">old</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Your</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span>:    <span class=\"mf\">1.66.0</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">Minimum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">version</span>: <span class=\"mf\">1.68.2</span>\n<span class=\"o\">***</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">1825</span>: <span class=\"nc\">rustavailable</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but otherwise it seems to build with the older toolchain (I'm doing a rebuild now to confirm)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It will build, but Rust will not be enabled.</p>",
        "id": 351300876,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1681991728
