    {
        "content": "<p>oh, I see, I've enabled rust support and I'm testing it again</p>",
        "id": 351301892,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1681991977
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411477\">Miguel Ojeda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Testing.20the.20rustc.20upgrade/near/351300876\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It will build, but Rust will not be enabled.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>To clarify: if the config has been rewritten (e.g. via <code>menuconfig</code>). It can be surprising/confusing that <code>RUST</code> gets automatically disabled if the toolchain requirements are not met when reconfiguring, but it is how we were requested to set it up originally. We may want to change that if we are going to have a lot of upgrades.</p>",
        "id": 351305471,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1681992745
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By the way, we have a Quick Start guide at <a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/quick-start.html\">https://docs.kernel.org/rust/quick-start.html</a> that you may want to follow, instead of a third-party blog post.</p>",
        "id": 351305745,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1681992819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes, it's indeed surprising since I was sure I had <code>RUST</code> enabled in the config</p>",
        "id": 351310779,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1681993981
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is surprising and annoying that Rust is silently turned off by menuconfig. I was hit by that a few times. It would be much more helpful with a build error.</p>",
        "id": 351355031,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1682003397
    }
